---

# General Rules

Before making implementation changes:

* understand the current lifecycle stage;
* identify the requested scope;
* read the required project documentation;
* locate the relevant implementation plan;
* respect architectural and engineering boundaries;
* update documentation whenever repository knowledge changes.

Do not:

* implement undocumented architectural changes;
* invent engineering decisions;
* expand implementation scope.

When requirements are ambiguous, ask for clarification instead of guessing.
